
[1]anadiplosis

   ANADIPLO'SIS, n. [Gr. again, and double.]

   Duplication, a figure in rhetoric and poetry, consisting in the
   repetition of the last word or words in a line or clause of a sentence,
   in the beginning of the next; as, "he retained his virtues amidst all
   his misfortunes, misfortunes which no prudence could foresee or
   prevent.
